This topic explains how to install <%= vars.platform_name %> on AWS using Terraform.

## <a id="overview"></a> Overview

You can install <%= vars.platform_name %> on AWS with either the <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>) or <%= vars.k8s_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>) runtime.

To install <%= vars.platform_name %> on AWS using Terraform, do one of the following:

* Install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>. See [Install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform](#terraform-pas).
* Install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>. See [Install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform](#terraform-pks).

## <a id="terraform-pas"></a> Install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform

To install with <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Pivotal Operations Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.','-') %>/aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.','-') %>/aws/config-terraform.html).

## <a id="terraform-pks"></a> Install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> Using Terraform

To install with <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Ops Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.','-') %>/aws/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on AWS Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.','-') %>/aws/config-terraform.html).

## <a id="next"></a> Next Steps

After completing the procedures above, configure a runtime.

